sion:** Keep P1 defensive overlay active. Do not lift defensive posture until BTC net reclaims **>$15M** with broader participation. Treat ETH short-cover as deleveraging, not reversal. Treat SOL as current bearish risk leg. PM weekend block and config remain unchanged; PM copy sample is too small to override anything.\n\n**Next:** Watch `fc66` rotation. If BTC stays **<$10M** and SOL expands beyond **-$12M**, escalate from defensive overlay to broad risk-off copy posture for majors.\n\n## 2026-05-03 21:02 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Normalized RANGE/UP, P1 defensive conflict\n\n**Task:** Refresh P4 alpha after BTC normalized to RANGE/UP at 20:38 while P1 then broke the `$15M` distribution line, testing whether microstructure stays constructive or confirms defensive risk.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P4**.\n- Ran fresh `/home/ubuntu/clawd/scripts/alpha-signal-update.sh`.\n- Current alpha timestamp: **2026-05-03T21:02:39.105487+00:00**.\n- BTC price **$78,866.00**, 24h **+0.483%**; Fear & Gree",
